    "description": "<br>Are you an experienced&nbsp;<strong>Electrician?</strong><br>&nbsp;<br>Are you interested in an opportunity in <strong>Perth?</strong><br>&nbsp;<br>Recruitment Direct UK Ltd is a premier recruiter operating across the UK and we act for our client operating across Scotland.<br><br>We are seeking a qualified Electrician to join the maintenance team at a local authority. This position offers a structured work-life balance and may suit someone looking for reduced guaranteed hours, with the flexibility to take on additional work elsewhere if desired.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Key Details:<br> <br> <ul> <li>Hours: Monday to Thursday: 8:00 AM to 4:00 PM&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Friday: 8:00 AM to 1:00 PM</li> <li>Contract: Long-term with the possibility of offered full-time position&nbsp;</li> <li>Start Date: Dependent on Disclosure clearance (see below)</li> </ul> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Key Responsibilities:<br> <ul> <li>Carry out planned and reactive maintenance on electrical systems within the prison estate.</li> <li>Ensure compliance with safety regulations and prison security procedures.</li> <li>Diagnose and repair electrical faults as required.</li> <li>Work collaboratively with other maintenance staff and prison personnel.</li> </ul> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Requirements:<br> <ul> <li>Fully qualified Electrician (SVQ Level 3, City &amp; Guilds, or equivalent).</li> <li>18th Edition Wiring Regulations certification</li> <li>Ability to pass enhanced disclosure and security clearance checks:</li> <li>Must have a clean criminal record (no unspent convictions).</li> <li>No driving bans</li> <li>Security clearance typically takes 3-4 weeks.</li> <li>Some departments allow an immediate start with a basic disclosure (if already obtained).</li> </ul> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Who This Job Suits:<br> <ul> <li>Electricians looking for a stable, long-term position with set hours.</li> <li>Individuals comfortable working in a secure environment within the public sector.</li> </ul>",
